    "## 4. Weak picks + leakage check\n",
    "\n",
    "### Weak Picks Explanation\n",
    "Many of our top-ranked items (such as rank 2, 3, 7, 8, etc.) have `suggested_action` = `monitor` and are completely stable (`trend_direction == 'stable'`). Because our baseline heuristic gives significant weight to absolute search impressions (40%) and high positions (25%), any stable, high-authority page is automatically pushed to the top of the queue. This is a \"weak pick\" for a refresh queue, because the editor will waste time reviewing pages that do not actually require edits.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Leakage Verification\n",
    "We have verified that no future-window fields (e.g. `impressions_last_30d` or `clicks_last_30d`) or label-derived indicators (`trend_direction` / `trend_pct`) are used inside the scoring function or features. The model remains honest and depends only on prior-window authority and metadata."
   ]
